1.	Open Terminal using:
Ctrl + Alt + T

2.	Create a sample file:
nano file1.txt
Enter some text.
Save the file:
Press Ctrl + O → Enter → Ctrl + X

3.	Copy the file:
cp file1.txt file2.txt

4.	Verify copied content:
cat file2.txt

VERIFYING KERNEL API USAGE USING STRACE
To observe kernel system calls used by the cp command, the strace tool is used.
Run:
strace cp file1.txt file2.txt


touch exp3
echo "Hi, How are you?">exp3
cat exp3

cp exp3 exp3.1
cat exp3.1
strace cp exp3 exp3.1

ls
strace ls

mv exp3 exp3.1
cat exp3.1
strace mv exp3 exp3.1

